frameDefinitions: Blend of Rewards_and_punishments and Bodily_injury in which the Agent performs some action intended to cause Bodily harm to the Evaluee as a consequence of some action or belief of the Evaluee (the Reason).
This frame includes words for medical instruments--i.e. Instruments designed for  an institutional function or Purpose.
These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
An Executioner punishes an individual (Executed) with death as a consequence of some action of the Evaluee (the Reason).
frameExamples: The Sheriff <t>flogged</t> him for his crimes.
Use the <fex name='Inst'><t>stethoscope</t></fex> to check his lungs.
The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
listRoleDefinitions: The Agent is the person performing the intentional act.
Evaluee is the person or thing about whom/which a judgment is made. With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:
Typically, there is a constituent expressing the <fen>Reason</fen> for the Judge's judgment. It is usually a <ment>for</ment>-PP, e.g.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
This role identifies the medical <fen>Instrument</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
The <fen>Executioner</fen> is the individual who performs the execution.
The <fen>Executed</fen> is the person who is killed by the <fen>Executioner</fen> in retribution for the crime that the <fen>Executed</fen> was convicted of.
When the execution occurs.
Where the execution takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>You</fex> will be flogged for your actions.
The Sheriff flogged him <fex>for his crimes</fex>.
Use the <fex><t>stethoscope</t></fex> to check his lungs.
<fex>A basic washing</fex> can degrease your workclothes.
The prisoners were deloused <fex>in June and August</fex>.
Stu treated <fex>the lumber</fex> with magical waterproofing fairydust.
The truth is, <fex>we</fex> have all put them to death.
<fex>He</fex> was to be hanged in the morning.
